added.title: Clarence Loves Shoopy
added.description: When Clarence discovers that one of his neighbors is the grumpy school recess proctor Ms. Shoop - he gets a glimpse of her home life and decides the only things she's missing are some friends. Clarence sets out on a mission to match the cranky oddball Shoop with some new pals!

added.title: Public Radio
added.description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

added.title: Chad and the Marathon
added.description: When Chad realizes his lazy habits might be rubbing off on Clarence, he decides to participate in the Aberdale Marathon. However, the athletic Chad doesn't know the first thing about being a runner, and must enlist the help of Clarence to train!

added.title: Officer Moody
added.description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

added.title: Gilben's Different
added.description: Gilben's newly sprouted peach fuzz sparks a discussion about puberty that ultimately convinces Clarence to act more like an adult.

added.title: Cool Guy Clarence
added.description: When Clarence meets JT, the kid who mows their lawn, he finds a fast friend who shows him some cool new music, a new outlook on life and a sweet rat-tail! Clarence leans into the rat tail lifestyle, discovering a whole new side of Aberdale he never knew existed.

added.title: Just Wait in the Car
added.description: As Mary runs errands, Clarence waits in the car and struggles to fight boredom.

added.title: Missing Cat
added.description: When Chelsea accidentally lets her pet cat Crumbles out, the cat goes missing! Reluctant to ask for help, she struggles to find the cat before anyone realizes it's gone. It's up to cat whisperer Clarence to interject and find Crumbles, whether Chelsea wants his help or not!

added.title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
added.description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

added.title: Dare Day
added.description: With Jeff on vacation, Sumo and Clarence egg each other on in a series of increasingly absurd and extreme dares. But will one of them put a stop to this dare day, before it goes too far?

added.title: The Trade
added.description: After accidentally trading away Chad's favorite baseball card, Clarence has to trade it back! Determined to become an expert, Clarence transforms himself into a slick salesman, before facing the ultimate deal…

added.title: A Nightmare on Aberdale Street: Balance's Revenge
added.description: In this Halloween adventure, Clarence uses a special jack-o-lantern to enter the world of people's dreams. He discovers that something mysterious is causing his friends to have nightmares, and Clarence needs to stop it!

added.title: Chadsgiving
added.description: Clarence is excited for Thanksgiving Dinner with Chad's parents, but Chad is worried that their unusually laid back demeanor and bizarre customs will make him look irresponsible by association.

added.title: A Sumoful Mind
added.description: When Jeff realizes Sumo's new classes have been rubbing off on Sumo, he attempts to further foster this newfound intellectual Sumo! But will Clarence's lowbrow antics reverse Jeff's hard work?

added.title: Animal Day
added.description: Clarence feels the call of the wild - and decides to live a new life, free of the hustle and bustle of the modern world. Recruiting a few friends, Clarence sets out to find a new place to live his feral life, but quickly realizes he lacks some basic survival skills.

added.title: The Tunnel
added.description: After Clarence accidentally knocks Belson's new video game down a storm drain, Belson enters the large underground sewer tunnel to retrieve it. When Belson doesn't return, Clarence must decide whether or not to go in after him.

added.title: Talent Show
added.description: Clarence throws a big talent show in his yard to showcase all the fun hidden talents of his friends. But when Brady claims he's talentless, Clarence sets out to prove that everyone has something special to share!

added.title: RC Car
added.description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

added.title: Dog King Clarence
added.description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

added.title: Trampoline
added.description: Mary buys a new trampoline for the family, but an accident lands her on the couch for a while. Determined to fight the boredom of being stuck indoors, she discovers her neighbor may be hiding something exciting.

added.title: Clarence the Movie
added.description: When Clarence starts to play around with his home video camera, he becomes increasingly drawn into the world of filmmaking. From talking toys, to real actors, to documentary subjects, Clarence is determined to find the right style to tell his story!

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Brains TV
added.description: After a marathon of classic sitcom episodes, Clarence becomes stuck as alter-ego "Clarry," an obnoxiously overacting sitcom version of himself. It's up to his friends and family to help him snap out of it, or face life with a new Clarence.

added.title: Etiquette Clarence
added.description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

added.title: Video Store
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo visit their local video store to rent a movie, but discover it's all rented out! Each of them have a different idea of what tape to bring home, and must enlist the help of a tie breaker to figure it out.

added.title: Anywhere but Sumo
added.description: When Clarence realizes Sumo has made a new group of friends at his new school, he becomes jealous and confused. Will Clarence accept a school life void of Sumo, or scheme his way into making their friendship work?

removed.title: El teatro de la perdicion
removed.description: Cuando la pandilla investiga la historia de Cueva Cristal, la momia de un fraile franciscano cobra vida para terminar lo que había empezado.

removed.title: Arte oscuro
removed.description: El mundo de las artes visita Cueva Cristal con un misterio: una obra de arte que intenta destruir a su creador. iY con Scooby como integrante de una banda emo, las cosas se vuelven bastante pesadas!

removed.title: Alienigenas entre nosotros
removed.description: Con la ayuda de la madre de Vilma, la pandilla investiga la posibilidad que exista de vida extraterrestre en Cueva Cristal.

removed.title: Corazon de maldad
removed.description: Dinamita y Fabulman se unen a la pandilla de Misterios S. A. para resolver el misterio de un horrible robot mitad humano mitad dragón que está aterrorizando la ciudad.

removed.title: Una bestia de otra dimension
removed.description: Después de que la pandilla de Misterio S.A. se separa, los chicos deciden seguir con su vida y visitar una universidad cercana, pero se ven obligados a retrasar sus planes cuando una misteriosa criatura llamada Char Gar Gothakon aterroriza el lugar con sus gritos, que destruyen todo a su paso.

removed.title: La cancion misteriosa
removed.description: Una criatura llamada Qué Horrífico está convirtiendo en monstruos a todos los niños de Cueva Cristal, y aterrorizando a todos los adultos de la ciudad.

removed.title: Caballero Televisivo 3
removed.description: Batman está más interesado en ver televisión que en participar de su fiesta de cumpleaños.

removed.title: La casa de la bruja pesadilla
removed.description: Vilma y Hotdog Water trabajan para el Sr. E con el fin de recuperar una pieza de museo proveniente de Moscú. Pero la pieza, una bruja y su casa, cobran vida y acechan Cueva Cristal.

removed.title: La telarana del Tejedor de Suenos
removed.description: Cuando la pandilla se pone a trabajar para resolver el misterio del "Tejedor de Sueños", quien hace que los ciudadanos destruyan todo lo que más quieren, Fred recibe la visita de sus verdaderos padres.

removed.title: El devorador
removed.description: Cuando la chef célebre favorita de Cueva Cristal tiene un accidente en la cocina, se desatan extraños incidentes.

removed.title: Proximo Idolo de la Liga de la Justicia: Parte 2
removed.description: La competencia se enciende cuando Robin hace lo imposible por ganar.

removed.title: Una noche en la macabra montana
removed.description: La pandilla de Misterios S.A. escala el Monte Diabla para resolver el misterio de un oscuro Ángel de la Destrucción y su misterioso galeón español, pero lo que en verdad encuentran ies otra pieza del Disco!

removed.title: La noche en que el bufon lloro 2: Lagrimas de perdicion
removed.description: El Bufón Llorón ha regresado para vengarse: ha secuestrado a ciudadanos de Cueva Cristal. Pero cuando su presa es Daphne, la pandilla no pierde tiempo y resuelve el misterio.

removed.title: La ira de Krampus
removed.description: La extraña aparición de un malvado hombre-cabra llamado Krampus obliga a la pandilla de Misterios S.A. a salir a buscar todas las piezas del Disco Planisférico.

removed.title: Liberados
removed.description: iEs el fin del mundo! Y nuestros héroes deben trabajar juntos para por fin darse cuenta de que su amor mutuo es el verdadero Corazón del Jaguar.

removed.title: Dia del Trabajo
removed.description: Llegó el Día del Trabajo, y Robin les enseña a los demás Titanes la importancia del trabajo.

removed.title: El ataque del hombre sin cabeza
removed.description: Cuando el Dr. Rick Spartan, el aventurero favorito de Fred, comienza a enseñar Biología en la secundaria de Cueva Cristal, la pandilla se da el gusto de conocerlo en persona. Después de una larga conversación con Fred, Spartan decide invitar a la pandilla a cenar a su casa.

removed.title: Trono de Huesos
removed.description: Cuando los demás Titanes comienzan a escuchar música heavy metal, Robin les advierte sobre los peligros.

removed.title: La Noche Negra de los Cazadores
removed.description: En busca del Corazón del Jaguar, la pandilla de Misterios S.A. se dirige al sur de la frontera.

removed.title: El escape de la mansion
removed.description: Cuando la pandilla se propone descubrir qué le pasó al grupo original de Misterio S.A. en uno de sus últimos casos, la desaparición de la familia Darrow y su mansión, ocurrida 75 años atrás, queda atrapada en la mansión Darrow subterránea, que está llena de trampas.

removed.title: La verdadera identidad
removed.description: Un asesino de vanguardia llamado Obliteratrix ataca a la pandilla, que termina investigando el misterio del tesoro embrujado con ayuda de H. P. Hatecraft.

removed.title: Caballero TV 2
removed.description: Batman y el Comisionado Gordon hacen una pijamada para mirar sus programas de televisión favoritos.

removed.title: El ataque del gnomo
removed.description: La pandilla va a la Feria de Caballeros Reales de Cueva Cristal, donde un gnomo maligno está paralizando a todos los que llevan disfraces de piratas.

removed.title: Cuidado con la bestia de las alcantarillas
removed.description: Un mutante de cieno que vive bajo Cueva Cristal atrapa en un capullo a quien se atraviese en su camino.

removed.title: La danza de los no muertos
removed.description: Una famosa banda cuyos miembros murieron en un accidente aéreo en Crystal Cove regresa para aterrar a la ciudad en el trigésimo aniversario de su muerte.

removed.title: Cuando la cigarra llama
removed.description: La pandilla investiga una plaga de insectos mortales en Cueva Cristal que amenaza a los empleados de la empresa Destroido, que fabrica los cereales favoritos de Shaggy y Scooby.

removed.title: El Hodag del terror
removed.description: Buscando a la mítica bestia Hodag, la pandilla de Misterios S.A. encuentra algo mucho más valioso: ila cuarta pieza del Disco Planisférico!

removed.title: El dinero o la vida
removed.description: Un dandi, un inglés elegante del siglo XVIII, acecha las carreteras de Cueva Cristal.

removed.title: La noche en que el bufon lloro
removed.description: La pandilla está dividida y Cueva Cristal está acechada por un malvado hombre-bebé llamado "Bufón Llorón". El alcalde convoca a Misterios S.A. para que regrese.

removed.title: La Pandilla Salvaje
removed.description: Fred invita a los chicos a la segunda cita con Daphne, que termina embelesada por Obnarb, el líder de la Pandilla Salvaje, un grupo de motociclistas orcos de visita en la ciudad. Cuando alguien asalta el arsenal y roba un arma muy peligrosa, los miembros de la Pandilla Salvaje se convierten en los principales sospechosos. Ahora Misterio S. A. debe resolver el enigma, salvar a la Pandilla Salvaje y encontrar al ciclista orco impostor.

removed.title: Las Puertas de la Oscuridad
removed.description: El profesor Pericles y lo que queda de la pandilla de Misterios S.A. buscan la entrada a las cavernas donde están enterrados el tesoro maldito y la Entidad del Mal.

removed.title: La venganza del Hombre Cangrejo
removed.description: Durante un torneo de vóley en la playa de Cueva Cristal, un monstruoso cangrejo gigante ataca a todos los presentes.

removed.title: Los cocodrilos
removed.description: La pandilla recibe una encomienda del señor E. que contiene un nuevo bolso hecho en Gatorsburgo.

removed.title: Proximo Idolo de la Liga de la Justicia: Parte 1
removed.description: La Liga de la Justicia organiza un concurso de talentos para encontrar a un superhéroe digno de unirse al equipo.

removed.title: El Fenomeno de Cueva Cristal
removed.description: Los chicos van en busca del tesoro escondido de Cueva Cristal pero "el Fenómeno" los detiene.

removed.title: Titanes Clasicos
removed.description: Para demostrar su punto de vista sobre los dibujos animados clásicos de superhéroes, iControl Freak envía a los Titanes a una versión antigua de Jóvenes Titanes en Acción!

removed.title: La batalla de los Humungonautas
removed.description: Dos monstruos gigantes, bautizados Humungonautas por el sheriff Stone, atacan Cueva Cristal.

removed.title: El fantasma de la carretera
removed.description: Un misterioso Camión Fantasma que espanta a la gente de las carreteras, aterroriza a Cueva Cristal.

removed.title: La leyenda de Alice May
removed.description: Fred es víctima de un romance estudiantil cuando una chica nueva, Alice May, se enamora de él, exasperando a Daphne.

removed.title: La pocion de la juventud
removed.description: Un vampiro anda suelto en Cueva Cristal y roba objetos aparentemente sin sentido.

removed.title: El sabueso endemoniado
removed.description: Un misterioso y violento perro aterroriza a Cueva Cristal. El sheriff Stone acusa a Scooby-Doo y lo arresta.

removed.title: Finales del Club de Misterios por Resolver
removed.description: Enfermo y en cama la noche anterior a la final estatal del Club de Misterios por Resolver, Scooby sueña que va a la competencia para rescatar a sus amigos de las garras del diabólico Lord Infernicus.

removed.title: El hombre del espejo
removed.description: En el sótano de una mansión embrujada, la pandilla encuentra un extraño espejo con mente propia.

removed.title: El secreto del dragon
removed.description: Cuando la estudiante de intercambio Mai Li llega a Cueva Cristal, Shaggy se encariña con ella. Una cena ofrecida por la familia Blake se ve interrumpida por el Mago Rojo, que les advierte que no se acerquen al Corazón de Dragón, que juró proteger a toda costa.

removed.title: La justicia muerta
removed.description: El fantasma del mejor sheriff de Cueva Cristal, Dead Justice, volvió de su tumba para hacer que el sheriff Bronson renuncie a su cargo. Dead Justice atrapa a los delincuentes más buscados de la ciudad y un monstruo, y el sheriff Stone se siente humillado.

removed.title: Una aparicion en Cueva Cristal
removed.description: Una sombría y extraña figura ataca al papá de Fred en su casa, y los chicos deben llegar al fondo del misterio.

removed.title: El oso monstruoso
removed.description: El alcade recluta a la pandilla de Misterios S.A. para que investigue el misterio del Oso Espeluznante, un oso mutante que está atemorizando la ciudad de Destroido.

removed.title: A traves de la cortina
removed.description: Nuestros héroes siguen el rastro de Pericles y sus secuaces a través de cavernas subterráneas.

removed.title: El fantasma aterrorizante
removed.description: Las Hex Girls, la banda preferida de Vilma, llegan a Cueva Cristal para dar un concierto.

removed.title: El Caballero de la Tele
removed.description: Batman y el comisionado Gordon salen a presenciar varios sucesos que ocurren cerca de Jump City.

removed.title: La creciente oscuridad
removed.description: Cuando el Demonio del Cementerio ataca a la pandilla, los chicos evitan hacer el típico "perfil del villano", incluso cuando el sospechoso perfecto se encuentra frente a sus ojos.

removed.title: El canto de la sirena
removed.description: Velma se siente sola sin su pandilla ni sus amigos. Cuando recibe un mensaje sobre "peces monstruosos" en los alrededores de una plataforma petrolera, decide investigar por su cuenta y descubre a la sirena que le envió el mensaje.

removed.title: Terrores nocturnos
removed.description: Debido a una avalancha, la pandilla de Misterios S.A. se ve atrapada en una tenebrosa biblioteca. Allí se encuentra la pandilla rival, Solución de Misterios, quienes también están buscando el Disco Planisférico.

removed.title: La venganza de Afrodita
removed.description: Cuando la ciudad entera es presa del hechizo de amor de Afrodita, Scooby-Doo y el recién escapado de prisión profesor Pericles, deben salvar a la pandilla y a la ciudad.

removed.title: El juicio de Grim
removed.description: Cuando un alocado y fantasmal juez puritano llamado Hebediah Grimm atemoriza a los jóvenes de Cueva Cristal en la Calle de los Enamorados, la pandilla de Misterios S.A. toma cartas en el asunto.

removed.title: Noche de miedo
removed.description: Scooby y Shaggy ganan un concurso de ensayos y el premio es una cena con Vincent Van Ghoul. Cuando llegan a su mansión, los ataca un monstruo que se hace llamar Nightfright, lo que hace que Van Ghoul revele que usó el concurso para lanzar un nuevo programa de TV del que Nightfright no es parte.

removed.title: La amenaza de la manticora
removed.description: Cuando el alcalde Jones compra un antiguo templo persa en el misterioso sitio web de "La Espeluznante y Horrorosa Tierra del Terror" de Cueva Cristal, descubre que una mantícora se está comiendo a los visitantes del parque. Sin alternativa, le pide a Fred y a su pandilla que lo ayuden a capturarla.

removed.title: La manada del horror
removed.description: Una manada sobrenatural de calaveras de ganado desata el caos en Cueva Cristal.

removed.title: Pesadilla en rojo
removed.description: Nuestros héroes permiten que los hipnoticen para poder entrar al mundo de los sueños.

removed.title: Come Undone
removed.description: It's the end of the world! And our heroes must work together to ultimately realize their love for each other is the true Heart of the Jaguar.

removed.title: Dance of the Undead
removed.description: When Crystal Cove's favorite southern celebrity chef has a cooking accident, strange incidents ensue.

removed.title: Heart of Evil
removed.description: Dr. Zin, of Jonny Quest fame, wreaks havoc on Crystal Cove.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo! and Kiss Rock and Roll Mystery
removed.description: When a ghoul begins to terrorize an amusement park, the Mystery Inc. gang come head to head with the legendary rock group, KISS, who claim they're also there to solve the mystery. Now the two groups must learn to work together as the clues lead them on a cosmic journey to another dimension.

removed.title: Ghost of the Red Baron
removed.description: The members of Mystery, Inc. join with the Three Stooges to thwart the ghost of the Red Baron, a daring evildoer who has scared away all of farmer Sawyer's crop-dusting pilots in an effort to pressure Sawyer into leaving his land.

removed.title: The Night the Clown Cried II: Tears of Doom
removed.description: Crybaby Clown is back with a vengeance. He's kidnapping all sorts of folks all over Crystal Cove - namely a therapist, a hairdresser, a plastic surgeon and a publicist!

removed.title: Scooby-Doo Meets the Addams Family
removed.description: Scooby and the gang consent to spend the weekend as housekeepers in the spooky home of the Addams Family so Morticia and Gomez Addams can take a much needed vacation in Okeefenokee swamp.

removed.title: The Exterminator
removed.description: Scooby and the gang stop on Sunset Boulevard to help troubled motorist Don Adams. But the engine is infested with some vengeful, metal-munching termites that completely devour the motor. Scooby and the gang volunteer to help Adams with his next exterminator job.

removed.title: The Frickert Fracas
removed.description: When Jonathan Winters invites Scooby and the gang to stay at the farm of his friend, Maude Frickert, they mistakenly believe it will be a vacation from haunted houses and spooky characters. They soon learn differently when vandalizing scoundrels and truly scary scarecrows overrun Maude's farm.

removed.title: The Night the Clown Cried
removed.description: With the gang split up, Crystal Cove is being tormented by an evil-man-baby called Crybaby Clown!

removed.title: Scooby-Doo and the Witch's Ghost
removed.description: When the gang meets up with famous fright-writer Ben Ravencroft, he invited them to New England for his hometown's bit Autumn Harvest Festival. Things take a supernatural detour when they learn the place is haunted by Ben's ancestor Sarah! Will the mystery reveal that Sarah was a good-hearted healer or a spell-casting witch? Before you can say, "Scooby Snacks", the gang is on the case tangling with bumbling mummies, monster turkeys and (zoinks) a ghostly secret hidden in the Ravencroft family's past! Grooving to the tunes of the movie's rocking band The Hex Girls, it's Scooby-Doo at his spellbinding, spine-tingling, super-sleuthing best!

removed.title: A Good Medium Is Rare
removed.description: The gang finds a dog with a diamond collar. They return the dog to the owner, Phyllis Diller, who lives in an old, creepy house. Scooby and friends tour the home and discover it is apparently haunted by Phyllis' ex-husbands. Scooby unravels the mystery of these strange occurrences.

removed.title: The Devouring
removed.description: When a Gluten Demon rises up and attacks famous foodie Francilee Jackson, our gang has to try to stop this monster before it consumes all the bread, pasta and other tasty foodstuffs in Crystal Cove.

removed.title: Theater of Doom
removed.description: Life imitates art in Crystal Cove's annual Haunted Historical Pageant.

removed.title: Night on Haunted Mountain
removed.description: When Ethan and Gary are mountain climbing Mount Diabla out in the desert, they're attacked by Lilith, a dark-winged angel of destruction.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo and the Reluctant Werewolf
removed.description: Scooby and Shaggy become race car drivers at the annual Monster Rally when the vampire, Dracula, hatches a plot to create a new werewolf. The pair encounter a host of classic horror-movie monsters in their attempt to stop Dracula.

removed.title: Scarebear
removed.description: The mayor of Crystal Cove has his camping trip ruined by the evil Scarebear and the gang is on the case.

removed.title: Dark Night of the Hunters
removed.description: Searching for the Heart of the Jaguar, the Mystery Incorporated gang heads down south of the border.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo Meets Laurel and Hardy
removed.description: Scooby and the gang join wits with Laurel and Hardy, newly appointed bellhops at a Vermont ski lodge, to track an abominable snowman by the name of Bigfoot!

removed.title: The Gathering Gloom
removed.description: When the gang is at Crystal Cove Cemetery watching a free screening of an old Vincent Van Ghoul movie with half the town, they are attacked by the Graveyard Ghoul!

removed.title: The Haunted Showboat
removed.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang, along with the rock group Josie and the Pussycats, battle ghosts haunting the Dixie Queen Showboat on the Missouri River. The mystery begins when the 100-year-old ghost of Injun Joe, a Mark Twain character from Tom Sawyer, along with another ghost, drag chains, move objects and make scary noises.

removed.title: Stand and Deliver
removed.description: A dandy, well-groomed, 18th century Englishman haunts the highways of Crystal Cove.

removed.title: The Haunted Candy Factory
removed.description: Cass Elliot, former singer with The Mamas and the Papas, hires Scooby-Doo and the Mystery, Inc. kids to investigate two living globs of green cotton candy creating a sticky mess at her Sugarplum Candy Company.

removed.title: House of the Nightmare Witch
removed.description: A Russian museum exhibit comes to life. It's an evil Russian witch by the name of Baba Yaga. The gang hunts Baba Yaga in Crystal Cove's Haunted Forest of Doom only to end up being the hunted.

removed.title: The Caped Crusader Caper
removed.description: Scooby and Mystery Inc. meet the terrible twosome, Penguin and Joker, on a camping trip in the forest. To stop the evildoers, the kids enlist the aid of those crusaders against crime, Batman and Robin. Penguin and Joker plan to steal the newest invention of Professor Flakey, a flying suit but Scooby and Shaggy's bumbling antics foil the criminals' scheme.

removed.title: The Horrible Herd
removed.description: A heard of supernatural skull cattle wreak havoc on Crystal Cove.

removed.title: The Haunted Horseman in Hagglethorn Hall
removed.description: The gang must prove a ghostly horseman haunting Hagglethorn Castle is a fake apparition. Otherwise, Davy Jones' uncle will have to sell the Scottish fortress, once a thriving tourist spot, to the greedy Duke of Strathmore.

removed.title: Grim Judgement
removed.description: Hebediah Grim, a menacing Puritannical ancestor of Crystal Cove, terrorizes Lovers Lane.

removed.title: Through the Curtain
removed.description: Traveling through the underground caverns, our heroes trail Pericles and company.

removed.title: The Ghostly Creep from the Deep
removed.description: The members of Mystery, Inc. join forces with the Harlem Globetrotters on the eerie banks of a haunted swamp to battle supernatural spirits unleashed by the ghost of Redbeard the pirate!

removed.title: The Hodag of Horror
removed.description: A traveling curio wagon arrives in Crystal Cove and a carnie-barker by the name of Gene Shepherd unveils the Hodag, a beast supposed to be found in the wilds of Wisconsin. It's a horrible fake. But when it comes to life and starts stealing, the gang investigates.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo Meets Jeannie
removed.description: On a trip back in time, Scooby and the gang meet a genie, Jeannie, as they travel to Persia to help a prince fight evil ghosts.
